   THE STORY OF WEYRICH
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Saying that "Nixon went to China," Bush added that Tower's record of support for Pentagon spending hikes could be overturned. But Weyrich's attack raised anew the issue of Tower's fitness for the job, after two days of testimony the week of Jan. 25, 1989 in which Tower won broad praise from committee members . Weyrich, president of the conservative Free Congress Foundation, testified that Tower's behavior makes him unfit to lead the Pentagon into an era of belt-tightening and management reform .
